									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/henryhemming/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Hemming-BW-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" alt="Henry Hemming" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/henryhemming/">Henry Hemming</a></h6>
										Henry Hemming is the author of seven books, including <em>Agents of Influence</em>, <em>Agent M</em>, and <em>The Ingenious Mr. Pyke</em>, which landed on the <em>New York Times</em> monthly espionage bestseller list, as well as <em>Four Shots in the Night</em>. He has written for <em>The Economist</em>, <em>FT Magazine</em>, and <em>The Washington Post</em>, and has given interviews on Radio 4’s <em>Today Programme</em> and NBC’s <em>Today Show</em>.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
							<br class="clear"/>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div>
													<div class="sidebar_content ad_bottom">
								<li id="custom_ads-24" class="widget Custom_Ads"><div class="htlad-LH_PP_F"></div></li>
							</div>
